{
  "message": "test(conformance): add FP-P2D-127 fixture packets for reshape/pivot/rolling/expanding/ewm\n\nAdds 18 fixture packets under crates/fp-conformance/fixtures/\npackets/ covering the six new oracle operations wired up in the\npreceding commit. Each JSON file matches the FixtureOperation /\nPacketFixture schema from fp-conformance/src/lib.rs and names\nthe oracle op it targets.\n\nPivot / crosstab / get_dummies coverage:\n\n- fp_p2d_127_dataframe_pivot_table_strict (renamed to\n  _pivot_table_mean_missing_strict alongside strict and\n  multi-values siblings), _pivot_table_sum_strict,\n  _pivot_table_multi_values_strict, _pivot_table_margins_strict,\n  _pivot_table_fill_hardened, _pivot_table_unsupported_agg_\n  hardened. Strict fixtures pin the numeric / sum / mean-with-\n  missing / margins behaviours; hardened fixtures pin the\n  fill_value and the unsupported-aggfunc error paths.\n- fp_p2d_127_dataframe_crosstab_strict, _crosstab_null_labels_\n  hardened, _crosstab_normalize_index_strict so both the\n  ordinary frequency table and the normalize=\"index\" row-sum\n  variant are locked down, plus the null-label hardened arm.\n- fp_p2d_127_dataframe_get_dummies_column_order_strict and\n  fp_p2d_127_series_str_get_dummies_hardened covering one-hot\n  encoding column ordering and the sep-based series path.\n\nReshape coverage:\n\n- fp_p2d_127_dataframe_stack_strict and fp_p2d_127_series_\n  unstack_strict.\n\nRolling / expanding / ewm coverage:\n\n- fp_p2d_127_dataframe_rolling_mean_basic_strict,\n  fp_p2d_127_series_rolling_mean_basic_strict,\n  fp_p2d_127_series_rolling_sum_min_periods_strict: the three\n  rolling-window happy paths.\n- fp_p2d_127_series_expanding_count_strict locks in the\n  monotonic count semantic.\n- fp_p2d_127_series_ewm_mean_span_strict locks in EWMA with\n  the span parameter.\n\nAll packets share packet_id \"FP-P2D-127\" and reference the\noracle operations added in the previous commit; no\nimplementation / engine changes in this commit - pure fixtures.",
